						<summary>

						<p>Nandi pillar (south face) in the Viśvēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1113, Chaitra śu. 15, Thursday.</hi> However, the details are irregular.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record an endowment of land to the temple of Mahādēva.</p>						

